<root>
  <content id="runInTerm">
    <section class="main-content">

      <h2 id="runn-commandline-header">
        <a id="running-tests-comandline" class="anchor" href="#running-tests-comandline" aria-hidden="true"><span
                aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Running
        tests in commandline</h2>
      <div>
    <p>
      Start simple <code title="start in terminal">php run.php -c [config.json]</code> your tests. You can overwrite your config file with follow additional parameters:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        -d [directory] <em>path to test directory</em>
      </li>
      <li>
        -i [imagedirectory] <em>path to image directory vor captured screenshots</em>
      </li>
      <li>
        -s [seleniumhub][http://localhost:4444/wd/hub] <em>reset the target selenium hub.</em>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Here is a example config file:</p>
<pre>
<code title="example json" >
{
  "testonaut": {
    "browsers": [
      {
        "deviceName" : "Google Nexus 5",
        "name" : "chrome",
        "fullscreen" : "true",
        "dimension" : {
          "width" : "1024",
          "height": "768"
        }
      },
      {
        "name" : "firefox",
        "fullscreen" : "true",
        "dimension" : {
          "width" : "1024",
          "height": "768"
        }
      }
    ],
    "config": {
      "imageDir":"images",
      "testDir": "root/test/test2",
      "hub" : "http://localhost:4444/wd/hub"
    }
  }
}
</code>
</pre>
        <p>
          The Parameters <em>fullscreen</em> and <em>dimensional</em> are conflicting. If fullscreen is set,the dimension parameters are overwrite.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </content>
</root>